reenFromWeb?topicID=3587.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RF Question</span><hr size=1> By what right does one group claim ascendency over anouther?<br>
<br>
One one hand you have those who feel that by using a network of others keepng a particular avatar on line they have the &quot;right&quot; to the next RF spawn.<br>
<br>
On the other hand you have those who put their efforts into an attempt to time the spawn and show up within a specified time frame.<br>
<br>
So far I have seen a great deal of both general and personal rudeness on both sides...name calling, guilt trip tactics, blatent slander.  If this were a political forum I think the applicable term would be mudslinging.<br>
<br>
My quandry is this:  <br>
<br>
It is a well known method of camping the RF spawn to either have several people rotate logging in the avatar while the person who pays for the account sleeps/works or the person goes AFK and relies on others grouped in the zone to maintain the camp.  There are various permutations of these themes, but by and large I think it pretty much covers how a camp of several days is accomplished.<br>
<br>
How is this more &quot;right&quot; than the person, for whatever personal reasons, chooses a different method of capturing the spawn? ie: timing it.<br>
<br>
As far as I know RF is the only &quot;camp&quot; where the actual person who pays for an account can claim legitimacy of camping even though it is a fact that no one person can possibly maintain an active presence over a period of several days.<br>
<br>
It's also been demonstrated that the cleric community has so far been unable to create a system to ease the process of aquiring their epic within the framework set up by VI.<br>
<br>
The real problem with this whole issue, as I see it, is that personal agenda's are constantly getting in the way of resonable behaviour.  <br>
<br>
We have many examples of things that should get people banned from the game and yet are becoming acceptable actions to &quot;protect&quot; a camp.  People training the dispelling mobs over groups forming up and buffing while their people are still trying to get enough in the zone to beat them to RF.  People training mobs over other clerics who are in the zone in order to force them to &quot;respect&quot; anouthers &quot;camp&quot;.  Forming -real- KS groups who wait untill some other group kills the human RF then attacks the triggered dragon.<br>
<br>
Then you have those who interpret the mere presents of a person of anouther guild or even of particular guilds in the zone to be an intent by that guild to KS their camp.  And RF isnt even &quot;due&quot; for several days.<br>
<br>
I have personally witnessed all of these actions.<br>
<br>
Add to this mix that guides and GM's don't have a really consistent process for dealing with the RF issues.  Or at worse they don't seem to adhere to any process.<br>
<br>
Lets try this...next time you are &quot;camping&quot; RF, don't throw a fit when anouther person shows up in the zone.  Have at least one person of your &quot;camp&quot; log eveything.  If that person, or group of people start making directed comments that they actually intend to KS, then you have a legitimate reason to call in a guide.  If all they do is come sit and &quot;observe&quot;, you do not have a rational excuse to do or say anthing provocative.<br>
<br>
Because they have every right to be in that zone that you do.  This is not a red server after all.<br>
<br>
And lets be rational.  There is a difference in opinion about camping.  Your beliefs are really no more or less legitimate than the next person/group.<br>
<br>
Trying to force your way on others in this matter is really not a lot different from real life.  Look at Northern Ireland or Bosnia as examples of conflict created due to differences of belief.  You can also look there to see what happens when people hold onto ideas based on perceptions of history rather than a more &quot;evolved&quot; theory of personal interaction.<br>
<br>
If you do not have a killing force in zone at the time of the spawn, or can't get that killing force in place within a reasonable time...say 30 min's, then unless the other people are willing to extend more time to you, you lost.<br>
<br>
There is no other spawn in this game that attempts to grant legitemecy to a person who isn't actively at that spawn.  And claiming that you have been camping RF for xx days is really admitting that you personally have not been actively there.  Given human psysiology, there is no resonalble claim that &quot;you&quot; have been camping RF for several days.<br>
<br>
It's at that point where I think you lose the argument of a claim to RF to a person who chooses to &quot;time&quot; the spawn within a few hours.<br>
<br>
And just like you, this is my opinion.  Nothing more and nothing less.<br>
<br>
Your rational comments are welcome.  A continueing dialoge may help resolve the issue.  Best case would be VI actually paying attention to a player base that has a rational presentation including a better seolution than the current situation.<br>
<br>
Personal attacks on my &quot;honor&quot; for not &quot;respecting&quot; your opinion will be laughed at.  If thats all you can say then don't bother.  But you will.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.<br>
This is a personal opinion, and should not be thought of as any groups stated position. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 2081<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/28/02 6:49:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3587.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RF Question</span><hr size=1> Oh boy. Just what I needed. Another RF thread.<br>
