<br>
I personally wish guilds could agree the terms for a server wide rotation, accepted by all guilds, and end this minefield of acrimony and recrimination.<br>
<br>
Personally, I live in an idealised world, where the person who has served their time at the camp, ofton for days on end, has their camp respected, subject to the restriction you made below.<br>
_________________________<br>
If you do not have a killing force in zone at the time of the spawn, or can't get that killing force in place within a reasonable time...say 30 min's, then unless the other people are willing to extend more time to you, you lost.<br>
_________________________<br>
<br>
The fact that more than one person might have looked after that avatar is not that relevent.  Even if friends, guildies etc have taken over every now and again so you can sleep, eat, or just plain rest, I bet you that the true owner of the avatar will still be the person who spent the largest chunk of sleepless time at camp.<br>
<br>
The tone of you some of your post suggests you beleive that the person who has been there for 5 days straight, has no more right than the person who turns up 5 mins before the spawn.  That just seems to substitute natural justice for a 'might is right' approach.<br>
<br>
I wish all the clerics (who only need rage for their epic), would submit themselves to a serverwide random to determine a queue order for the spawn.  With the exercise not being repeated for the next set of clerics until all those clerics had got their epics, or failed trying.<br>
<br>
I'd probably impose a minimum cap too, say level 55.<br>
<br>
Pipe dreams of course.<br>
<br>
Ysall the Kind<br>
60 Ench<br>
