<br>
-----------------------------------------------<br>
By what right do one group claim ascendency over anouther? <br>
<br>
One one hand ya gots those who feel dat by usin' uh network o' others keepng uh particular avatar on line dey gots da &quot;right&quot; ta da next RF spawn. <br>
<br>
On da other hand ya gots those who put they efforts into an attempt ta tyme da spawn an' show up within uh specified tyme frame. <br>
<br>
So far I gots seen uh great deal o' both general an' personal rudeness on both sides...name calling, guilt trip tactics, blatent slander. If dis here wuz uh political forum I th'o't da applicable term would be mudslinging. <br>
<br>
My quandry iz this: <br>
<br>
It iz uh well known method o' camping da RF spawn ta either gots several peeps rotate logging in da avatar while da person who pays fo' da account sleeps/works or da person goes AFK an' relies on others grouped in da zone ta maintain da camp. There iz various permutations o' deez themes, but by an' large I th'o't it fine ass much covers how uh camp o' several days iz accomplished. <br>
<br>
How iz dis here mo' &quot;right&quot; than da person, fo' whatever personal reasons, chooses uh different method o' capturing da spawn? ie: timing it. <br>
<br>
As far as I know RF iz da only &quot;camp&quot; where da actual person who pays fo' an account can claim legitimacy o' camping even though it iz uh fact dat nahh one person can possibly maintain an active presence over uh period o' several days. <br>
<br>
It'salso been demonstrated dat da cleric community has so far been unable ta create uh system ta ease da process o' aquiring they epic within da framework set up by VI. <br>
<br>
The real problem wiff dis here whole issue, as I see it, iz dat personal agenda'siz constantly getting in da way o' resonable behaviour. <br>
<br>
We gots many examples o' things dat should git peeps banned from da game an' yet iz becoming acceptable actions ta &quot;protect&quot; uh camp. People training da dispelling mobs over groups forming up an' buffing while they peeps iz still trying ta git enough in da zone ta beat dem ta RF. People training mobs over other clerics who iz in da zone in order ta force dem ta &quot;respect&quot; anouthers &quot;camp&quot;. Forming -real- KS groups who wait untill some other group kills da human RF then attacks da triggered dragon. <br>
<br>
Then ya gots those who interpret da mere presents o' uh person o' anouther guild or even o' particular guilds in da zone ta be an intent by dat guild ta KS they camp. And RF ain't even &quot;due&quot; fo' several days. <br>
<br>
I gots personally witnessed all o' deez actions. <br>
<br>
Add ta dis here mix dat guides an' GM'sdon' gots uh really consistent process fo' dealing wiff da RF issues. Or at worse dey don' seem ta adhere ta any process. <br>
<br>
Lets try dis here...next tyme ya iz &quot;camping&quot; RF, don' throw uh fit when anouther person shows up in da zone. Have at least one person o' yo' &quot;camp&quot; log eveything. If dat person, or group o' peeps start making directed comments dat dey actually intend ta KS, then ya gots uh legitimate reason ta page in uh guide. If all dey do iz come sit an' &quot;observe&quot;, ya do not gots uh rational excuse ta do or say anthing provocative. <br>
<br>
Because dey gots every right ta be in dat zone dat ya do. This iz not uh red server afta all. <br>
<br>
And lets be rational. There iz uh difference in opinion about camping. Your beliefs iz really nahh mo' or less legitimate than da next person/group. <br>
<br>
Trying ta force yo' way on others in dis here matter iz really not uh lot different from real life. Look at Northern Ireland or Bosnia as examples o' conflict created due ta differences o' belief. You can also peep dere ta see what happens when peeps hold onto ideas based on perceptions o' history rather than uh mo' &quot;evolved&quot; theory o' personal interaction. <br>
<br>
If ya do not gots uh killing force in zone at da tyme o' da spawn, or can't git dat killing force in place within uh reasonable tyme...say 30 min 's, then unless da other peeps iz willing ta extend mo' tyme ta ya, ya lost. <br>
<br>
There iz nahh other spawn in dis here game dat attempts ta grant legitemecy ta uh person who ain't actively at dat spawn. And claiming dat ya gots been camping RF fo' xx days iz really admitting dat ya personally gots not been actively dere. Given human psysiology, dere iz nahh resonalble claim dat &quot;you&quot; gots been camping RF fo' several days. <br>
<br>
It'sat dat point where I th'o't ya lose da argument o' uh claim ta RF ta uh person who chooses ta &quot;time&quot; da spawn within uh few hours. <br>
<br>
And just like ya, dis here iz muh ma fuckin opinion. Nothing mo' an' nuttin' less. <br>
<br>
Your rational comments iz welcome. A continueing dialoge may he`p resolve da issue. Best case would be VI actually paying attention ta uh player base dat has uh rational presentation including uh bettah seolution than da current @#%$. <br>
<br>
Personal attacks on muh ma fuckin &quot;honor&quot; fo' not &quot;respecting&quot; yo' opinion will be laughed at. If thats all ya can say then don' bother. But ya will. <br>
<br>
Thank ya fo' yo' tyme. <br>
